Malaysia and Indonesia both claim sovereignty over the Celebes Sea islands.
The island restricts access to 80 divers and 40 staff to protect the coral reef and wildlife.
Sipadan, a top diving spot, is off the coast of Sabah, Malaysia.
The recent abduction of 20 hostages by armed men has sparked a search operation.
Among the hostages are South Africans, Germans, French, and Americans.
Malaysian and Philippine authorities are working together to track down the kidnappers.
The situation remains tense as efforts are made to secure the release of the hostages.
